    "culture_note": "Chale, numbers are your survival kit — traders count fast in Twi when you haggle, and knowing 1–10 cold means you won't pay 'ɔbroni price' (the inflated foreigner rate)."
  },
  "grammar_mechanics": {
    "focus": "Counting from one to ten",
    "explanation": "The Akan numerals one to ten are: baako, mmienu, mmiɛnsa, ɛnan, enum, nsia, nson, nwɔtwe, nkron, edu. They follow a noun when counting objects.",
    "patterns": [
      "1 baako · 2 mmienu · 3 mmiɛnsa",
      "4 ɛnan · 5 enum · 6 nsia",
      "7 nson · 8 nwɔtwe · 9 nkron · 10 edu"
    ]
  },
